---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="work" prompt="~/work">
  <div class="content">
    <section>
      <h2>Cloud & Infrastructure</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>AWS (EKS, ECS, EC2, IAM, Organizations, RDS, ElastiCache, MSK)</li>
        <li>GCP (BigQuery, IAM, service accounts)</li>
        <li>Terraform & OpenTofu — module design, multi-account patterns, Terraform Cloud</li>
        <li>Kubernetes (EKS, Karpenter, Helm, ArgoCD)</li>
        <li>Cloudflare (DNS, WAF, Terraform-managed)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>CI/CD & Automation</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Concourse</li>
        <li>Ansible — automation platform design, inner-sourcing at scale</li>
        <li>Bash, Python</li>
        <li>AI-assisted infrastructure automation (Claude Code, structured workflow authoring)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Observability & Security</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Datadog, PgAnalyze, Vantage</li>
        <li>PCI Level 1, SOC2, Bulletproof audit compliance</li>
        <li>Secrets management (AWS Secrets Manager, 1Password)</li>
        <li>Okta & IAM Identity Center (enterprise SSO)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Experience</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Underdog — Staff Engineer / Engineering Manager, 2022–present</li>
        <li>Comcast — Senior Engineer, 2016–2022 (with a Red Hat consulting stint in 2018)</li>
        <li>Urban Outfitters — DevOps Engineer, 2014–2016</li>
        <li>Earlier roles at Comcast, UPenn, Burlington, Costco — 2007–2014</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .content {
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  ul li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  ul li::before {
    content: '›';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
